          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Are first-party cookies going away?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Only third-party cookies are being phased out by browsers. First-party cookies remain fully supported in Chrome, Safari, Firefox, and Edge because they're essential for logins, sessions, and site functionality.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do I need cookie consent for first-party cookies?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes for non-essential first-party cookies. Under GDPR and ePrivacy, any cookie used for analytics, marketing, or personalization needs prior consent. Strictly necessary cookies (login, cart, security) are exempt.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What's the difference between first-party and third-party cookies?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>First-party cookies are set by the domain in the browser's address bar. Third-party cookies are set by other domains (like ad networks) loaded on the page. Browsers increasingly block third-party cookies but keep first-party ones.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long do first-party cookies last?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>It depends on how they're set. Session cookies disappear when the browser closes. Persistent cookies live until an explicit expiration date — up to 400 days in Chrome as of the Chrome 104 cookie lifetime limit.</p></div></div>
          </div>
